Expose aux-loss-free load-balancing (DeepSeek-V3 expert bias) CLI args.

The MoE core (router.py / finalize_model_grads.py) and TransformerConfig already
support a dynamic per-expert routing bias as an aux-loss-free load-balancing
strategy, but this fork's arguments.py does not expose the corresponding flags,
so the config always falls back to the dataclass defaults (disabled, softmax).

This patch adds three flags to the 'moe' argument group in
megatron/training/arguments.py (dest names match the TransformerConfig fields, so
core_transformer_config_from_args() picks them up automatically):
  --moe-router-score-function {softmax,sigmoid}  (default softmax)
  --moe-router-enable-expert-bias                (store_true)
  --moe-router-bias-update-rate <float>          (default 1e-3)

Enabling expert bias requires the sigmoid score function (enforced by
TransformerConfig). Use with --moe-router-load-balancing-type none for pure
aux-loss-free balancing (no aux loss).

diff --git a/megatron/training/arguments.py b/megatron/training/arguments.py
index 44c776f6c..8b5c6363f 100644
--- a/megatron/training/arguments.py
+++ b/megatron/training/arguments.py
@@ -2722,6 +2722,16 @@ def _add_moe_args(parser):
                        help='Determines the load balancing strategy for the router. "aux_loss" corresponds to the load balancing loss used in GShard and SwitchTransformer; "seq_aux_loss" corresponds to the load balancing loss used in DeepSeekV2, which computes the loss for each individual sample; "sinkhorn" corresponds to the balancing algorithm used in S-BASE, and "none" implies no load balancing. The default is "aux_loss".')
     group.add_argument('--moe-aux-loss-coeff', type=float, nargs='+', default=0.0,
                        help='Scaling coefficient for the aux loss: a starting value of 1e-2 is recommended.')
+    group.add_argument('--moe-router-score-function', type=str,
+                       choices=['softmax', 'sigmoid'], default='softmax',
+                       help='Score function for MoE routing ("softmax" or "sigmoid"). '
+                       'Aux-loss-free load balancing (expert bias) requires "sigmoid".')
+    group.add_argument('--moe-router-enable-expert-bias', action='store_true',
+                       help='TopK routing with a dynamic per-expert bias for aux-loss-free '
+                       'load balancing (DeepSeek-V3). The routing decision is based on the sum '
+                       'of routing scores and the bias. Requires --moe-router-score-function sigmoid.')
+    group.add_argument('--moe-router-bias-update-rate', type=float, default=1e-3,
+                       help='Update rate of the per-expert bias in aux-loss-free load balancing.')
